data.chText: 相册；影集；集邮簿；集物簿册
data.enText: a book in which you keep photographs, stamps, etc.

data.chText: （唱片或盒式磁带等上的）音乐专辑，歌曲专辑；歌集唱片
data.enText: a collection of pieces of music that have been recorded on one record, CD or cassette

simple_means.memory_skill: alb 白色 + um → 空白的东西 → 用来放东西的册子 → 相册

means: (唱片或盒式磁带等上的)音乐专辑

tr: a book of blank pages with pockets or envelopes
for organizing photographs or stamp collections etc
one or more recordings issued together
originally released on 12-inch phonograph records (usually with attractive record covers) and later on cassette audiotape and compact disc

value.def: An album is a record with about 25 minutes of music on each side. You can also refer to a collection of songs that is available on a record, cassette, or CD as an album .

example.ex: Chris likes music and has a large collection of albums and cassettes.
example.tran: 克里斯喜欢音乐，收集了大量的唱片和磁带。

value.def: An album is a book in which you keep things such as photographs or stamps that you have collected.

example.ex: Theresa showed me her photo album.
example.tran: 特雷莎给我看她的相册。

value.tran: （用于保存照片、邮票等的）专册，专辑簿

trans: 集邮册；贴票册；邮册；集邮簿；邮集

partsOfSpeech.dec: alb 白色 + escent 开始出现…的 → 开始变白 → 发白的
alb 白色 + um → 空白的东西 → 用来放东西的册子 → 相册
